      "description": "This Mazda RX-7 FD3S is a superlative example of 90s engineering, featuring a numbers-matching 13B-REW rotary powerplant with its sequential twin-turbocharger setup intact and delivering linear boost across the rev range. The chassis remains structurally flawless, retaining its factory-spec double-wishbone suspension and Torsen limited-slip differential for neutral handling characteristics. Meticulously maintained, the drivetrain exhibits zero vacuum leaks or cooling system fatigue, while apex seal compression remains within optimal factory tolerances. Finished in its original paint with a completely preserved interior, this specimen represents a turnkey investment for the discerning collector seeking peak JDM performance and mechanical purity.",
